headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 38 points, making a season-high eight 3-pointers, and Jaylen Brown added 31 points as the Boston Celtics beat the Indiana Pacers 118-101 on Saturday night, snapping the Pacers’ six-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum and Jaylen Brown power Celtics to 118-101 win over Pacers

events.name: New York Knicks at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 39 points, Jalen Brunson had 33 and the New York Knicks won their fourth straight game, beating the Washington Wizards 121-105 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 39 points, Brunson has 33 to lead Knicks to 4th straight win, 121-105 over Wizards

headlines.description: — The 76ers need a better plan to win games without Joel Embiid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen, Sexton have double-doubles to lead Utah past the 76ers 120-109 with Embiid out

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun scored 21 points and the Houston Rockets overcame 48 points from Giannis Antetokounmpo to beat the Milwaukee Bucks 112-108 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets overcome Antetokounmpo's 48 points, beat slumping Bucks 112-108
